ut 1122":"okolo 1122","about 1120":"okolo 1120","1218":"1218","Arborea, Sardinia, Italy":"Arborea, Sardegna, Itálie","Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy":"Logudoro, Sardegna, Itálie","Sardegna, Itália":"Sardegna, Itálie","Pisa, Tuscany, Italy":"Pisa, Toscana, Itálie"},"da":{"–1163":"–1163","1101–1163":"1101–1163","1110–1182":"1110–1182","1120–1191":"1120–1191","1122–1193":"1122–1193","1124–Male":"1124–Afdød","1128–1218":"1128–1218","–1136":"–1136","–Female":"Afdød","1110":"1110","1120":"1120","1163":"1163","30 May 1136":"30. maj 1136","1193":"1193","1182":"1182","1191":"1191","1128":"1128","1136":"1136","1124":"1124","1101":"1101","about 1128":"omkring 1128","1122":"1122","about 1124":"omkring 1124","about 1122":"omkring 1122","about 1120":"omkring 1120","1218":"1218","Arborea, Sardinia, Italy":"Arborea, Sardegna, Italien","Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy":"Logudoro, Sardegna, Italien","Sardegna, Itália":"Sardegna, Italien","Pisa, Tuscany, Italy":"Pisa, Toscana, Italien"},"nl":{"–1163":"–1163","1101–1163":"1101–1163","1110–1182":"1110–1182","1120–1191":"1120–1191","1122–1193":"1122–1193","1124–Male":"1124–Overleden","1128–1218":"1128–1218","–1136":"–1136","–Female":"Overleden","1110":"1110","1120":"1120","1163":"1163","30 May 1136":"30 mei 1136","1193":"1193","1182":"1182","1191":"1191","1128":"1128","1136":"1136","1124":"1124","1101":"1101","about 1128":"circa 1128","1122":"1122","about 1124":"circa 1124","about 1122":"circa 1122","about 1120":"circa 1120","1218":"1218","Arborea, Sardinia, Italy":"Arborea, Sardegna, Italië","Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy":"Logudoro, Sardegna, Italië","Sardegna, Itália":"Sardegna, Italië","Pisa, Tuscany, Italy":"Pisa, Toscana, Italië"},"en":{"–1163":"–1163","1101–1163":"1101–1163","1110–1182":"1110–1182","1120–1191":"1120–1191","1122–1193":"1122–1193","1124–Male":"1124–Deceased","1128–1218":"1128–1218","–1136":"–1136","–Female":"Deceased","1110":"1110","1120":"1120","1163":"1163","30 May 1136":"30 May 1136","1193":"1193","1182":"1182","1191":"1191","1128":"1128","1136":"1136","1124":"1124","1101":"1101","about 1128":"about 1128","1122":"1122","about 1124":"about 1124","about 1122":"about 1122","about 1120":"about 1120","1218":"1218","Arborea, Sardinia, Italy":"Arborea, Sardinia, Italy","Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy":"Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy","Sardegna, Itália":"Sardinia, Italy","Pisa, Tuscany, Italy":"Pisa, Tuscany, Italy","nameMeanings":[{"name":"di","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Chinese:","Mandarin form of the surname 狄, a term referring to the tribes in ancient northern China: (i) from Di (狄), the name of an ancient state (thought to have been located in Hebei or Shandong province), which was granted to Xiao Bo or Kao Bo by King Cheng of Zhou (reigned 1042–1021  BC ). (ii) adopted as a surname by the Ku Di (庫狄) family during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iii) traced back to other minority ethnic groups in ancient northwestern China.","Mandarin form of the Chinese surname 邸, meaning ‘official residence’ in Chinese: (i) from placename Di (邸), the name of a county (unidentified location). (ii) said to be borne by some descendants of Kujula Kadphises (called 丘就郤 or 邸就郤 in Chinese, 30–<i>c.</i> 80  AD ), founder of the Kushan Empire (one branch of the Yuezhi people originating from western China) located in Central Asia during the Eastern Han dynasty (25–220  AD )."],"variants":[{"name":"Chi","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Young, Dong, Yun, Cheng, Jae, Yong, Cheng Chung, Chi, Chun, Duk, Fang, Feng.  Korean Chung, Chong, Jae Hong, Moon, Myong, Pong, Shen, Yoo, Byung, Chang, Chol, Chong Hun.  Southeast Asian Phi, Hung, Ly, Tu, Denh, Do Van, Duong, Hao, Kieu, Mui, Nga, Phat.","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 池, meaning ‘moat’ in ancient Chinese: (i) acquired as a surname by people who lived beside a moat. (ii) from Chi (池), said to be the name of an ancient state (of unknown location and period). (iii) from the personal name Chi (池), personal name of a son of an official in the state of Qin during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 遲, meaning ‘late’ in Chinese: (i) borne by descendants of Chi Ren (遲任), a person who lived during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). (ii) shortened form of the Chinese compound surname Yu-Chi (尉遲), originally the name of a tribe from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China. (iii) from the second element of the personal name Zi Chi (子遲), style name of Fan Xu, a student of Confucius (551–479  BC )."]}]},{"name":"Pisa","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Carlo, Marco, Sabastian.","Italian and Spanish; Catalan (<b>Pisà</b>): habitational name from the city of Pisa in Tuscany. The city was probably founded by Greek colonists, but before coming under Roman control it was in the hands of the Etruscans, who probably gave it its name. At any rate, the placename is of obscure origin and meaning. Compare   Pisano  .","Italian: from the female personal name <i>Pisa</i>, from the name of the city (see 1 above)."],"variants":[{"name":"Piza","meanings":["Spanish; Catalan (<b>Pizà</b>): variant of   Pisa   and <b>Pisà</b>, habitational names from the city of Pisa in Tuscany. Compare   Pizano  ."]},{"name":"Pisano","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Antonio, Salvatore, Mario, Carmine, Carmela, Vito, Angelo, Armando, Rocco, Sal, Aldo, Domenic, Paolo, Rosario, Stefano.","Italian and Spanish (Cantabria and Palencia): habitational name for someone from Pisa in Tuscany, Italy (see   Pisa  ), from an adjectival form of the placename. Compare   Pizano  ."]}]},{"name":"Maria","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Maria  , of German origin but now also moderately popular in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maria Ebriaci di Pisa was born as the daughter of Ugo II degli Ebriaci di Pisa and Elena Orrubu. She had at least 4 sons with Rev Fr Gonario II di Lacon-Gunale, Judge of Torres. She died in 1163, in Sardinia, Italy."},"et":{"–1163":"–1163","1101–1163":"1101–1163","1110–1182":"1110–1182","1120–1191":"1120–1191","1122–1193":"1122–1193","1124–Male":"1124–Surnud","1128–1218":"1128–1218","–1136":"–1136","–Female":"Surnud","1110":"1110","1120":"1120","1163":"1163","30 May 1136":"30. mai 1136","1193":"1193","1182":"1182","1191":"1191","1128":"1128","1136":"1136","1124":"1124","1101":"1101","about 1128":"umbes 1128","1122":"1122","about 1124":"umbes 1124","about 1122":"umbes 1122","about 1120":"umbes 1120","1218":"1218","Arborea, Sardinia, Italy":"Arborea, Sardegna, Itaalia","Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy":"Logudoro, Sardegna, Itaalia","Sardegna, Itália":"Sardegna, Itaalia","Pisa, Tuscany, Italy":"Pisa, Toscana, Itaalia"},"fi":{"–1163":"–1163","1101–1163":"1101–1163","1110–1182":"1110–1182","1120–1191":"1120–1191","1122–1193":"1122–1193","1124–Male":"1124–Kuollut","1128–1218":"1128–1218","–1136":"–1136","–Female":"Kuollut","1110":"1110","1120":"1120","1163":"1163","30 May 1136":"30. toukokuuta 1136","1193":"1193","1182":"1182","1191":"1191","1128":"1128","1136":"1136","1124":"1124","1101":"1101","about 1128":"noin 1128","1122":"1122","about 1124":"noin 1124","about 1122":"noin 1122","about 1120":"noin 1120","1218":"1218","Arborea, Sardinia, Italy":"Arborea, Sardegna, Italia","Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy":"Logudoro, Sardegna, Italia","Sardegna, Itália":"Sardegna, Italia","Pisa, Tuscany, Italy":"Pisa, Toscana, Italia"},"fr":{"–1163":"–1163","1101–1163":"1101–1163","1110–1182":"1110–1182","1120–1191":"1120–1191","1122–1193":"1122–1193","1124–Male":"1124–Décédé","1128–1218":"1128–1218","–1136":"–1136","–Female":"Décédée","1110":"1110","1120":"1120","1163":"1163","30 May 1136":"30 mai 1136","1193":"